$ SQL Developer: User information directory
@ user information directory

The *SQL Developer user information directory* is the location that stores the user preference settings for → development/Software/Oracle-SQL-Developer[SQL Developer].

Apparently, the location of this directory can be specified with the `SQLDEVELOPER_USER_DIR` → development/environment-variable[environment variable]. If this variable is not set,
the location defaults to → Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData/Roaming/SQL-Developer[`$env:APPDATA\SQL Developer`] on → Windows.

sa:
  The function `get-SQLDeveloperUserInformationDirectory` of the → Windows/PowerShell/modules/personal/SQL-Developer[SQL Developer PowerShell module].

  Specifying the location of the user information directory in → development/Software/Oracle-SQL-Developer/directories/installation/sqldeveloper/bin/sqldeveloper_conf#sql-developer-conf-user-inf-dir[`sqldeveloper.conf`]

  The values of `ide.user.dir` and `ide.user.dir.var` (→ development/Software/Oracle-SQL-Developer/GUI/menu/Help/About/Properties[Help -> About -> Properties]).
